 The occupants of the vehicles sustained minor injuries but were treated at the scene. Recovery of the vehicles resulted in the closure of one lane on each side of the highway.  TRAC has issued a statement that both lanes in the eastbound direction have since been opened, only leaving one of the westbound lanes still closed. Motorists are warned of traffic in the area and are advised to drive with caution.      The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za   